fix: reconciler now detects when harness image was rebuilt and recreates the container. Added container_image_matches() to DockerManager — compares running container's image SHA against the latest local image ID. In the reconciler's ('running', true) branch, if images don't match, stops the agent (auto-removes container) and sets status to Stopped. Next reconcile cycle sees ('running', false) and starts a fresh container from the new image. This was the root cause of the user having to manually restart agents after build.sh — the image was rebuilt but containers kept running the old code.
